BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- China Saturday urged Malaysia to continue providing it with "thorough and exact information" about the missing flight MH370.Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Qin Gang said here at a press release that "Chinese technical specialists are on the way to Malaysia for helping the investigation."According to Qin, China will timely adjust its deployment of search and rescue forces and call on all countries possibly involved to lend their hands."We will also keep in touch with relevant countries and international organizations for making our own research and judgement," he said.